ier|short story of the same name]] by [[Stephen King]].<ref>https://www.allmovie.com/movie/stephen-kings-the-night-flier-v160483</ref>}}\n|-\n| ''[[Les deux orphelines vampires|The Two Orphan Vampires]]'' (Les deux orphelines vampires)\n| 1997.07.09\n| France\n| [[Jean Rollin]]\n| Alexandra Pic, Isabelle Teboul, Bernard Charnac\u00e9\n| {{small|Adaptation of Rollin's novel of the same name.}}\n|-\n| Blade\n\u3000\u3000''[[Blade (film)|Blade]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Blade II]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Blade: Trinity]]''\n|| <br>1998.08.21<br>2002.03.22<br>2004.12.08\n|| <br>United States<br>United States<br>United States\n|| <br>[[Stephen Norrington]]<br>[[Guillermo del Toro]]<br>[[David S. Goyer]]\n|| <br>[[Wesley Snipes]], [[Stephen Dorff]], [[Kris Kristofferson]]<br>[[Wesley Snipes]], [[Kris Kristofferson]], [[Ron Perlman]]<br>[[Wesley Snipes]], [[Kris Kristofferson]], [[Jessica Biel]]\n|| <br>{{small|Based on the [[Marvel Comics]] character.<br>First sequel.<br>Second sequel.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Razor Blade Smile]]'' \n| 1998.09.19\n| United Kingdom\n| [[Jake West]]\n| [[Eileen Daly]], [[Christopher Adamson]], Heidi James\n| {{small|A very low budget independent film which pays homage to the [[Hammer Film Productions|Hammer]] lesbian vampire films of the 1970s.}}\n|-\n| Vampires\n\u3000\u3000''[[Vampires (1998 film)|Vampires]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Vampires: Los Muertos]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Vampires: The Turning]]''\n|| <br>1998.10.30<br>2002.09.25<br>2005.05.03\n|| <br>United States<br>United States<br>United States\n|| <br>[[John Carpenter]]<br>[[Tommy Lee Wallace]]<br>Marty Weiss\n|| <br>[[James Woods]], [[Daniel Baldwin]], [[Sheryl Lee]]<br>{{small|[[Jon Bon Jovi]], [[Cristi\u00e1n de la Fuente]], [[Natasha Gregson Wagner]]}}<br>[[Colin Egglesfield]], Stephanie Chao, [[Roger Yuan]]\n|| <br>{{small|Also known as ''John Carpenter's Vampires''<br>First sequel.<br>Second sequel.}}\n|-\n| ''[[The Wisdom of Crocodiles]]'' \n| 1998.11.27\n| United Kingdom\n| [[Po-Chih L