lio Majano]]\n| [[Alberto Lupo]], Susanne Loret, [[Sergio Fantoni]]\n| {{small|A stripper is horribly disfigured in a car accident. A brilliant scientist develops a treatment that restores her beauty and then falls in love with her.}}\n|-\n| ''[[The Playgirls and the Vampire]]'' (L'ultima preda del vampiro)\n| 1960.11.28\n| Italy\n| [[Piero Regnoli]]\n| [[Lyla Rocco]], Walter Brandi, Maria Giovannini\n| {{small|Five beautiful showgirls are trapped by a storm and find refuge in a creepy old castle inhabited by Count Gabor, his assistant and a vampire.}}\n|-\n| ''[[El mundo de los vampiros|The World of the Vampires]]'' (El mundo de los vampiros)\n| 1961\n| Mexico\n| [[Alfonso Corona Blake]]\n| [[Guillermo Murray]], [[Mauricio Garces]], Erna Martha Baumann\n| {{small|About a vampire, Count Sergio Subotai, who seeks revenge against the descendant of an enemy family. The hero is a musician who knows how to play a piece of music that can kill vampires. }}\n|-\n| ''[[Slaughter of the Vampires]]'' (La strage dei vampiri) \n| 1962.02.06\n| Italy\n| [[Roberto Mauri]]\n| Walter Brandi, [[Dieter Eppler]], [[Graziella Granata]]\n| {{small|Later re-released as ''Curse of the Blood Ghouls''.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Santo vs. las Mujeres Vampiro|Santo vs. the Vampire Women]]'' (Santo vs. las Mujeres Vampiro)\n| 1962.10.11\n| Mexico\n| [[Alfonso Corona Blake]]\n| [[El Santo|Santo]], [[Lorena Vel\u00e1zquez]], [[Jaime Fern\u00e1ndez (actor)|Jaime Fern\u00e1ndez]]\n| {{small|A professor recruits a professional masked wrestler named [[El Santo]] to protect his daughter from vampires that are intent on kidnapping her and marrying her to the devil.}}\n|-\n| The Bloody Vampire\n\u3000\u3000''The Bloody Vampire'' (El vampiro sangriento)<br>\n\u3000\u3000''The Invasion of the Vampires'' (La invasi\u00f3n de los vampiros)\n|| <br>1962<br>1963\n|| <br>Mexico<br>Mexico\n|| <br>[[Miguel Morayta]]<br>[[Miguel Morayta]]\n|| <br>Bego\u00f1a Palacios, Erna Martha Bauman, Ra\u00fal Farell<br>Erna Martha Bauman