neuve]], [[David Bowie]], [[Susan Sarandon]]\n| {{small|A love triangle between a doctor who specializes in sleep and aging research and a vampire couple.}}\n|-\n| ''[[The Keep (film)|The Keep]]'' \n| 1983.12.16\n| United Kingdom/United States\n| [[Michael Mann]]\n| [[Scott Glenn]], [[Alberta Watson]], [[J\u00fcrgen Prochnow]]\n| {{small|Based on the [[F. Paul Wilson]] [[The Keep (Wilson novel)|novel of the same name]].}}\n|-\n| ''[[Bloodsuckers from Outer Space]]'' \n| 1984.10\n| United States\n| Glen Coburn\n| Thom Meyes, [[Dennis Letts]], Laura Ellis\n| {{small|A science fiction/black comedy/horror film.}} <ref>https://www.allmovie.com/movie/bloodsuckers-from-outer-space-v6189</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Lifeforce (film)|Lifeforce]]'' \n| 1985.06.21\n| Australia/United States\n| [[Tobe Hooper]]\n| [[Steve Railsback]], [[Peter Firth]], [[Frank Finlay]]\n| {{small|From the writer of ''Aliens'' and the director of ''Poltergeist''. Also known as ''Lifeforce: Space Aliens''.}}\n|-\n| Fright Night\n\u3000\u3000''[[Fright Night]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Fright Night Part 2]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Fright Night (2011 film)|Fright Night]]''<br>\n\u3000\u3000''[[Fright Night 2: New Blood]]''\n|| <br>1985.08.02<br>1988.12.08<br>2011.08.19<br>2013.10.01\n|| <br>United States<br>United States<br>United States<br>United States<br>\n|| <br>[[Tom Holland (director)|Tom Holland]]<br>[[Tommy Lee Wallace]]<br>[[Craig Gillespie]]<br>[[Eduardo Rodr\u00edguez (director)|Eduardo Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|| <br>[[Chris Sarandon]], [[William Ragsdale]], [[Amanda Bearse]]<br>[[Roddy McDowall]], [[William Ragsdale]], [[Traci Lind]]<br>[[Anton Yelchin]], [[Colin Farrell]], [[Christopher Mintz-Plasse]]<br>[[Will Payne (actor)|Will Payne]], [[Jaime Murray]], [[Sean Power (actor)|Sean Power]]\n|| <br>{{small|A [[Cult film|cult classic]].<br>Sequel featuring a female vampire out to avenge her brother.<br>Remake of the 1985 film.<br>Direct-to-video [[Remake|re-imagining]] of the earlier films.}}\n|-\n| ''[[A Polis