attinson]], [[Billy Burke (actor)|Billy Burke]]<br>[[Kristen Stewart]], [[Robert Pattinson]], [[Taylor Lautner]]<br>[[Kristen Stewart]], [[Robert Pattinson]], [[Taylor Lautner]]<br>[[Kristen Stewart]], [[Robert Pattinson]], [[Taylor Lautner]]<br>[[Kristen Stewart]], [[Robert Pattinson]], [[Taylor Lautner]]\n|| <br>{{small|Based on the [[Twilight (Meyer novel)|novel of the same name]].<br>Based on the novel ''[[New Moon (novel)|New Moon]]''.<br>Based on the novel ''[[Eclipse (Meyer novel)|Eclipse]]''.<br>Based on the first half of the novel ''[[Breaking Dawn]]''.<br>Based on the second half of the novel ''[[Breaking Dawn]]''.}}\n|-\n| ''[[The Librarian: Curse of the Judas Chalice]]'' \n| 2008.12.07\n| United States\n| Marco Schnabel\n| [[Noah Wyle]], [[Bob Newhart]], [[Jane Curtin]]\n| {{small|A TV movie about a librarian who encounters a vampire while searching for an ancient artifact called the Judas Chalice.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Against the Dark]]'' \n| 2009.02.10\n| United States\n| [[Richard Crudo]]\n| [[Steven Seagal]], [[Tanoai Reed]], Jenna Harrison\n| {{small|An epidemic disease has overwhelmed humanity, turning nearly everyone into infected bloodthirsty creatures who resemble vampires and zombies.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Blood (2009 film)|Blood]]'' (\u30d6\u30e9\u30c3\u30c9)\n| 2009.04.29\n| Japan\n| Ten Shimoyama\n| [[Aya Sugimoto]], [[Guts Ishimatsu]], [[Jun Kaname]]\n| {{small|A supernatural action film.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Thirst (2009 film)|Thirst]]'' (\ubc15\uc950) \n| 2009.04.30\n| South Korea\n| [[Park Chan-wook]]\n| [[Song Kang-ho]], [[Kim Ok-bin]], [[Kim Hae-sook]]\n| {{small|Loosely based on the novel ''[[Th\u00e9r\u00e8se Raquin]]'' by [[\u00c9mile Zola]].}}\n|-\n| ''[[Daybreakers]]'' \n| 2009.09.11\n| Australia/United States\n| [[The Spierig Brothers]]\n| [[Ethan Hawke]], [[Willem Dafoe]], [[Claudia Karvan]]\n| {{small|In a futuristic world that has been overrun by vampires, a vampiric corporation sets out to capture and farm the remaining humans while at the same time 