olo]], [[Michael Cerveris]]<br>Nick Damici, [[Connor Paolo]], Laura Abramsen\n|| <br>{{small|An orphaned young man is taken under the wing of a vampire hunter.<br>Sequel.}}\n|-\n| ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire]]'' \n| 2010.10.09\n| Canada\n| [[Bruce McDonald (director)|Bruce McDonald]]\n| [[Matthew Knight]], [[Vanessa Morgan]], [[Atticus Mitchell]]\n| {{small|A [[Teletoon]] channel movie.}}\n|-\n| ''[[We Are the Night (film)|We Are the Night]]'' (Wir sind die Nacht) \n| 2010.10.14\n| Germany\n| [[Dennis Gansel]]\n| [[Karoline Herfurth]], [[Nina Hoss]], [[Jennifer Ulrich]]\n| {{small|A modern-day film about a clique of young, rich and pretty female vampires.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Midnight Son]]'' \n| 2011.03.04\n| United States\n| Scott Leberecht\n| Zak Kilberg, Maya Parish, [[Larry Cedar]]\n| {{small|A young man is confined to a life of isolation, due to a very rare skin disorder.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Priest (2011 film)|Priest]]'' \n| 2011.05.13\n| United States\n| [[Scott Stewart (director)|Scott Stewart]]\n| [[Paul Bettany]], [[Karl Urban]], [[Lily Collins]]\n| {{small|Based on the South Korean [[Priest (manhwa)|comic of the same name]].}}\n|-\n| ''[[Monster Brawl]]''\n| 2011.07.23\n| Canada\n| Jesse T. Cook\n| [[Dave Foley]], [[Art Hindle]], [[Robert Maillet]]\n| <ref>https://www.allmovie.com/movie/monster-brawl-v549234</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Moth Diaries (film)|The Moth Diaries]]'' \n| 2011.09.06\n| Canada/Ireland\n| [[Mary Harron]]\n| [[Lily Cole]], [[Sarah Gadon]], [[Sarah Bolger]]\n| {{small|Based on the 2002 [[The Moth Diaries|novel of the same name]] by [[Rachel Klein (novelist)|Rachel Klein]]}}\n|-\n| ''[[Red Tears]]'' (\u30ec\u30c3\u30c9\u30fb\u30c6\u30a3\u30a2\u30fc\u30ba\uff5e\u7d05\u6d99) \n| 2011.10.24\n| Japan\n| Takanori Tsujimoto\n| [[Natsuki Kato]], [[Yuma Ishigaki]], [[Yasuaki Kurata]]\n| {{small|Two detectives hunt down a serial killer.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Vampire Dog]]'' \n| 2012.02.16\n| Canada\n| Geoff Anderson\n| Collin MacKechnie, [[Julia Sarah Stone]], [[Amy Matysio]]\n| {{small|A boy unwittingly adopts a 600-year-old talking vampire dog and soon discovers that when they face their fears, they can do ''anything''.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Empress Vampire]]'' \n| 2012.04.27\n| United States\n| Phil Condit\n| Ange Maya, Tom Cochran, Beau Nelson\n| {{small|The revelry of an upscale Halloween party is shattered by gunshots as two armed robbers attempt to fleece the well-to-do patrons of their money and jewels.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Kali the Little Vampire]]'' (Kali, le petit vampire) \n| 2012.04.29\n| {{small|France/Portugal/Canada/Switzerland}}\n| [[Regina Pessoa]]\n| [[Christopher Plummer]]\n| {{small|Animated short film about a boy who is not like the others that dreams about finding his place in the world.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Abraham Lincoln: Vampire Hunter (film)|Abraham Lincoln: Vampire Hunter]]'' \n| 2012.06.22\n| United States\n| [[Timur Bekmambetov]]\n| [[Benjamin Walker (actor)|Benjamin Walker]], [[Dominic Cooper]], [[Anthony Mackie]]\n| {{small|Based on the 2010 [[Mashup (book)|mashup novel]] [[Abraham Lincoln, Vampire Hunter (novel)|of the same name]].}}\n|-\n| ''[[Byzantium (film)|Byzantium]]'' \n| 2012.09.09\n| {{small|Ireland/United Kingdom/United States}}\n| [[Neil Jordan]]\n| [[Saoirse Ronan]], [[Gemma Arterton]], [[Sam Riley]]\n| {{small|A mother and daughter vampire duo move into a rundown hotel while hiding out from other vampires.}}\n|-\n| ''[[The ABCs of Death]]''\n| 2012.09.14\n| United States\n| Various directors\n| Various actors\n| <ref>https://www.allmovie.com/movie/the-abcs-of-death-v539966</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Rufus (2012 film)|Rufus]]'' \n| 2012.09.21 \n| Canada\n| Dave Schultz\n| Rory J. Saper, [[Kim Coates]], [[David James Elliott]]\n| {{small|A mysterious young man who turns up in a small town in Saskatchewan is eventually revealed to be a vampire.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Vamps (film)|Vamps]]'' \n| 2012.11.02\n| United States\n| [[Amy Heckerling]]\n| [[Alicia Silverstone]], [[Krysten Ritter]], [[Sigourney Weaver]]\n| {{small|About two socialite vampires living the good life in New York City.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Kiss of the Damned]]'' \n| 2012.11.07\n| United States\n| [[Xan Cassavetes]]\n| [[Jos\u00e9phine de La Baume]], [[Milo Ventimiglia]], [[Roxane Mesquida]]\n| {{small|A screenwriter staying in Connecticut to write a screenplay meets and falls in love with a woman, only to discover that she is a vampire who survives by drinking the blood of animals.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Only Lovers Left Alive]]'' \n| 2013.05.25\n| United Kingdom/Germany\n| [[Jim Jarmusch]]\n| [[Tilda Swinton]], [[Tom Hiddleston]], [[Mia Wasikowska]]\n| {{small|A romance between two vampires.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Black Water Vampire]]'' \n| 2014.01.24\n| United States\n| Evan Tramel\n| [[Bill Oberst Jr.]], Danielle Lozeau, Andrea Monier\n| {{small|A documentary film crew investigates a series of brutal killings known as the Black Water Murders.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Vampire Academy (film)|Vampire Academy]]'' \n| 2014.02.07\n| United States/United Kingdom\n| [[Mark Waters]]\n| [[Zoey Deutch]], [[Lucy Fry]], [[Danila Kozlovsky]]\n| {{small|Based on the series of novels of the same name by [[Richelle Mead]]}}\n|-\n| ''[[What We Do in the Shadows]]'' \n| 2014.06.19\n| New Zealand\n| [[Jemaine Clement]], [[Taika Waititi]]\n| Taika Waititi, Jemaine Clement, [[Rhys Darby]]\n| {{small|Horror/comedy/\"mockumentary\" film about a group of vampires who are sharing a flat in [[Wellington]].}}\n|-\n| ''[[A Girl Walks Home Alone at Night]]'' \n| 2014.11.21\n| United States\n| [[Ana Lily Amirpour]]\n| [[Sheila Vand]], Arash Marandi, [[Mozhan Marn\u00f2]]\n| {{small|The first Iranian vampire/Western film.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Bloodsucking Bastards]]'' \n| 2015.01.23\n| United States\n| Brian James O'Connell\n| [[Fran Kranz]], [[Joey Kern]], Emma Fitzpatrick\n| {{small|A down on his luck cubicle worker and his slacker best friend discover that their new boss is a vampire who is turning their co-workers into the undead.}}\n|-\n| ''[[Koisuru Vampire|Vampire in Love]]'' (\u604b\u3059\u308b